title: ICE: `rustc_specialization_trait` and circular associated type

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: F-rustc_attrs
labels.description: Internal rustc attributes gated on the `#[rustc_attrs]` feature gate.

labels.name: S-has-mcve
labels.description: A Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example has been found for this issue

labels.name: T-types
labels.description: Relevant to the types team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: requires-internal-features
labels.description: This issue requires the use of internal features

body:
### Code [[Playground link]](https://play.rust-lang.org/?edition=2021&gist=dfeae3d7de9324a5f43e3937618e8857) ```Rust #![feature(min_specialization, rustc_attrs)] #[rustc_specialization_trait] pub trait Trait {} struct Struct where Self: Iterator::Item>, {} impl Trait for Struct {} ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.64.0 (a55dd71d5 2022-09-19) binary: rustc commit-hash:
